frameDefinitions: A Fire burns Fuel, resulting in damage and possibly complete destruction of the Fuel.
A fire which burns and requires an emergency-type response.
The words in this frame describe acts (or situations characterized by acts) that cause injury or harm.
An Assailant physically attacks a Victim (which is usually but not always sentient), causing or intending to cause the Victim physical damage.
Due to chemical, nuclear, or other reactions, an Explosive explodes, potentially causing damage to the surrounding area.
frameExamples: A fire that started on Saturday afternoon, the High Glade Fire - located on the Mendocino National Forest's Upper Lake Ranger District - continued to <t>burn</t> actively on Sunday.
Research on whether concealed carry laws increase gun <t>violence</t> among gang members has been inconclusive.
As soon as he stepped out of the bar he was <t>set</t> upon by four men in ski-masks.
The bomb <t>exploded</t> in the middle of the plaza.
